<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="section-2" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Functions</title>
    <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Understanding how the starter code works</p></li>
      <li><p>Begin to understand the purpose of the functions, <c>setup</c>, <c>draw</c>, <c>canvas</c>, <c>background</c></p></li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <p>There are two <term>function definitions</term> in the code window: setup and draw.</p>
  <pre>
    <code>
      function setup() {
         ...
      }

      function draw() {
         ...
      }
    </code>
  </pre>     
  <p>
    The statement inside the setup function, <c>createCanvas</c>, is executed one time, 
    while the statement inside the draw function, <c>background</c>, is executed repeatedly 
    (this is often referred to as an infinite loop).    
  </p>
  <p><c>createCanvas(400,400)</c> is a <term>function call</term>. It calls a built-in function 
     from the p5 library. It has two arguments inside it's parentheses, 400 and 400.
     The first argument makes a canvas that is 400 <term>pixels</term> wide and 400 
     <term>pixels</term> tall. As you recall, it is the gray square to the right of the 
     code window. 
  </p>

  <p>MCQ WHAT IS THE OTHER FUNCTION CALL IN THIS PROGRAM?</p>
  <p>MCQ WHAT IS THE ARGUMENT TO THIS FUNCTION CALL?</p>   

  <p>For the following, the canvas will appear <alert>below</alert> the code window, which 
    is different from the p5 editor</p>
 <program xml:id="p5js-modify-starter-code" interactive="activecode" language="html">

    <preamble visible="no">
      <![CDATA[<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <script src="external/p5.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>]]>
    </preamble>

    <code>
<![CDATA[<script>

  function setup() {
    createCanvas(400, 300);
  }

  function draw() {
    background(220);
  }
  
</script>]]>
    </code>

  </program>

  <p>Arguments are separated by commas, so the number of commas will always be one less than
     the number of arguments.    </p>
</section>